    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"130384\">Riccardo Brasca</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.60.281.20-.20X.20.3A.20.E2.84.A4.5BX.5D.29.2EtoPowerSeries.20.3D.201.20-.20.28PowerSeries.2EX.20.3A.20.E2.84.A4.E2.9F.A6X.E2.9F.A7.29.60/near/483712435\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Strange that we have <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/RingTheory/PowerSeries/Basic.html#Polynomial.coe_add\">Polynomial.coe_add</a> but not <code>coe_sub</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I would guess this is because of the overhead of creating a new section with <code>Ring</code> instead of <code>Semiring</code> assumptions, and people being lazy (I know I've been guilty of this in the past)</p>",
        "id": 483721323,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1732201935
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"566592\">Fangming Li (John)</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/.60.281.20-.20X.20.3A.20.E2.84.A4.5BX.5D.29.2EtoPowerSeries.20.3D.201.20-.20.28PowerSeries.2EX.20.3A.20.E2.84.A4.E2.9F.A6X.E2.9F.A7.29.60/near/483718242\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Actually showing <code>(1 - X : ℤ[X]).toPowerSeries = 1 - (PowerSeries.X : ℤ⟦X⟧)</code> is a small goal in the process of the formalisation of Hilbert polynomials. I guess I will push these along with my contents on Hilbert polynomials.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This one is so small and easy that it's surely better to PR it now.</p>",
